  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Readiness To Proceed**\n\nNow that the linting is complete and the structure is validated, I\'m ready to summarize my findings. Before I finalize everything, I\'m making sure that the data structure is flexible and adaptable to the client\'s needs. Specifically, I\'m making sure it can easily accommodate images and info for a specific Instagram page, such as `veneza.barbearia`.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the landing page for Clube Veneza Barbearia, establishing an elegant, premium aesthetic inspired by your reference site. \n\nHere is what was built:\n- **Premium Identity**: Implemented a dark, sophisticated visual theme (using deep zinc and amber accents) paired with the elegant \"Playfair Display\" font for headings and clear \"Inter\" for body text. High-quality imagery is used throughout to set the tone.\n- **Location-First Flow**: Created an intuitive 2-step process. The user first selects their desired unit (with photos and address). Once selected, the page smoothly scrolls down and reveals only the plans active for that specific unit.\n- **Clear Monthly Plan Cards**: The plans are showcased using individual rich cards that feature their own imagery, explicitly state they are monthly subscriptions (`/ m\303\252s`), highlight their specific features, and link out to your existing payment page.\n- **Easily Editable Data**: The locations and plans are structured so that you can easily plug in real photos, exact addresses, and specific plan names for Veneza Barbearia by updating `src/data.ts`."
